# Commit messages

- Never add **Made-with: Cursor**, **Made with Cursor**, or **Co-authored-by: Cursor** (or similar) to commit subjects or bodies.
- Use the project format in `docs/agile/GIT_STRATEGY.md`: `{type}({scope}): {what} — {story-id}`.
- Optional `Co-Authored-By:` lines for non-Cursor tools are fine if your team agrees; avoid Cursor-specific trailers.
- If the environment injects a `Made-with: Cursor` line anyway, strip it with `bash scripts/strip-made-with-from-HEAD.sh` (Git Bash), or commit using the real Git binary (e.g. on Windows: `"%ProgramFiles%\Git\mingw64\bin\git.exe"`) so `git commit` / `git commit-tree` are not intercepted.
